    <Option value="model_sonucu_AFs_835321c5_ef76_4fa4_9d4c_21644a4a42f4" name="select_the_layer_covering_selected_active_fires" type="QString"/>
    <Option value="yangin_bolgeleri___smoothed_aydin__Grid_Statistics__492a7de7_68cf_4a46_aa84_722ccbdb8f66" name="select_the_layer_showing_delimited_fire_zones_doundaries" type="QString"/>
    <Option value="10" name="specify_the_number_of_intervals_for_the_fire_progressing_map" type="int"/>
    <Option value="50" name="specify_the_resolution_for_fpm_in_raster_grid_format" type="int"/>
  </Option>
  <Option name="groupBoxes"/>
  <Option name="help" type="Map">
    <Option value="Burak Beyhan" name="ALG_CREATOR" type="QString"/>
    <Option value="&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;>&#xa;&lt;html>&lt;head>&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; />&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;>&#xa;&lt;/style>&lt;/head>&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'MS Shell Dlg 2'; font-size:8.25pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Ubuntu Sans'; font-size:11pt;&quot;>This model helps you to produce Fire Progression Maps (FPM) provided that you have the layer covering the Active Fires (AF) data compiled for a region and the layer showing the wildfire zones delimited properly. Once you select the AFs, you should specify the layer covering these AFS together with the layer showing the wildfire zones and the number of intervals that will be used for the depiction of FPM. On the base of these inputs, the model will produce sub-daily FPM in both raster grid and vector format showing the progression of the fire according the speficied number of intervals.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:'Ubuntu Sans'; font-size:11pt;&quot;>&lt;br />&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot; font-family:'Ubuntu Sans'; font-size:11pt;&quot;>The model also requires two python scripts produced for the creation thematic maps according to the spectral color ramp. These script files (FPM Vector Legend.py and FPM Raster Legend.py) are included in FPM bundle created for the creation fire progression maps. In the bundle there are three models; (1) Delimitation of Burned Areas, (2) Pooling MODIS and VIRRS and (3) Production of Fire Progression Maps.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;/body>&lt;/html>" name="ALG_DESC" type="QString"/>
    <Option value="Burak Beyhan" name="ALG_HELP_CREATOR" type="QString"/>
    <Option value="Version 2.0" name="ALG_VERSION" type="QString"/>
